AB  - By using the preliminary guidelines set forth in previous research for the formative evaluation of academic progress using curriculum-based measurement (CBM) procedures, the present research tested the "goodness of fit" of those guidelines for use with first grade students in the regular education classroom. Group C consisted of 63 first grade students in three classrooms who were administered CBM math probes twice, once in the fall and once in the spring, as part of a larger school-wide norming study. Group M consisted of 19 first grade students who were monitored weekly by their classroom teacher using the same CBM math probes. Academic growth rates were analyzed using multiple regression procedures. Student slopes were examined to determine how well linear and quadratic relationships modeled student progress. The results supported the generalizability of past findings to a similar grade and population. Suggestions for future research are discussed.
