AB  - Evaluated 4 procedures designed to help 29 poor spellers from Grades 4–8 improve their achievement on weekly tests: (a) a pretest over the week's spelling words followed in 2 days by the regular weekly test; (b) a positive practice procedure in which Ss were required to correct any misspelled word on the weekly test by writing out its correct spelling, part of speech, phonetic spelling, complete definition, and correct usage in 5 different sentences; (c) a pretest, positive practice of the pretest, and the weekly test; and (d) a pretest, positive practice of the pretest, weekly test, and positive practice of the weekly test. The pretest/positive practice/test/positive practice procedure was the most effective, producing a 14% increase in spelling achievement. The pretest/positive practice/test (11% increase) and positive practice (10% increase) procedures were of near equal effectiveness. The pretest procedure produced no increase. (18 ref) (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2016 APA, all rights reserved)
