AB  - Evaluated the mathematics achievement effects of principal components of mastery learning and student team learning in a year-long randomized experiment with 588 9th graders. The components were formative tests, corrective instruction for nonmasters, summative tests (mastery), and practice in 4-member heterogeneous teams, and team rewards (teams). A 2 × 2 (mastery by teams) factorial experiment compared mastery, teams, teams + mastery, and a control treatment. All methods used the same materials and schedule of teaching, worksheets, and test. A nested ANCOVA indicated significant achievement main effects for teams but not for mastery. No mastery by teams or pretest by treatment interactions were found. Results support the instructional effectiveness of team work and team rewards characteristic of R. E. Slavin's (1983; also see record [rid]1984-07975-001[/rid]) method of student team learning. (30 ref) (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2016 APA, all rights reserved)
