AB  - 40 daily matching objective type tests were given to students in a course in general psychology. The scores made by the 173 students with complete records were divided consecutively into 8 blocks of 5 each. Cases were then arranged into quartiles according to average score for semester. Mean block standard deviations were computed for the individuals in each quartile. Variability of scores increased from the highest to the lowest quartile (rho = - .90). This relationship also held true for individual variability and average scores (r = - .40 ± .04). From this it would appear that daily testing stimulates learning-morale and interest in course subject matter. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2016 APA, all rights reserved)
